article.headline: Alabama A&amp,M 88, Oakwood 81
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Jonathan Inman came off the bench to score 20 points, including getting a key bucket in the overtime period, to lead Alabama A&M to an 88-81 victory over Oakwood Saturday night. The game was tied at 76 at the end of regulation, but the Bulldogs outscored Oakwood 12-5 in the overtime period. Leading scorer for Alabama A&M (1-2) was Evan Hilton with 17 points, while Mickell Gladness had a double-double with 13 points and 13 rebounds. Trent Simpson added 11 points for the Bulldogs and Desmond Jackson had 10. Oakwood's Dewitt Henley was the game's leading scorer as he also recorded a double-double with 26 points and 10 rebounds. Terrell Black added 16 points for Oakwood and James Doggette had 10.
